Part 2 of the loc attachments. made sure the hair is towel dry. In preparation for my clients favorite part. The scalp massage using #luxuryofchoice products and the scalp oil. Essential oils Mixing with the natural sebum oill of the scalp in order to  Stimulate blood flow and hair growth. And it’s very relaxing. I’ve had plenty of clients tell me that it helps with their migrain headaches.  The second part, is retwisting I don’t twist it all the way through because I will be combing out the ends later. So no point in doing extra work. I try to keep the ends in the early buding stage.  #Another speed trial… blink and you will miss it😁. Do you know someone that would enjoy this style? Throwback Thursday… I prefer to do color prior to starting the loc process. Many times when trying to do color to hair that hasn’t fully locd yet. You run the risk of washing almost if not all the starter locs or twist in order to wash the color out properly. When It comes to color either do it before the starter locs or at least until the hair is well into the budding phase #locnation #starterlocs #retwist #dreads #dreadstyles #menwithlocs

Do I have to cut the portion of my hair that is still permed? my response. Cutting or trimming the texturized portion of the hair does not help with or hinder the locking process. For many depending on the hair texture, it gives it what many would refer to as goddess locs. But understanding that as the locs mature I can create weak points starting from the point where the processed hair starts to the end of the loc. but with proper maintenance it reduces the probability of that outcome… so go ahead and loc your hair 😁 #locnation #starterlocs #goddesslocs #locnationstan #luxuryofchoice

Part 1 of loc repair. This is one of the techniques I use when  we have breakage, the loc that is being repaired doesn’t have enough hair at the point of breakage to reattach. We’re using a small amount of Afro kinky hair to create another anchor in order to prevent slippage after the attachment is complete .  One of the causes of slippage after loc attachments are do to not having enough hair to properly crochet into the loc in the first place.  Part 2, I will display one of the many options available after a loc is lost do to lack of maintenance or other variables.  Stay tune for part 2 since we don’t have the loc to reattach. We will be creating the loc as we do the attachments…
Full videos will be available on YouTube soon.

#twostrandtwist #rope twist. In this case using 2 Locs while twisting each clockwise and overlapping them counter clockwise. Giving it a rope like appearance. It can be done with more than one strand of locs. It can be altered with 2 and 2 or 3 and 2 or more depeding on the size you are tying to achieve. #locnation #Locstyles #menwithlocs #retwist #locstyles  shout out to @jus_locs  for the spider fingers method of rope twisting…
